issue.title: fledgeForGpt: clarify contextual bids and IG signals comparison
issue.body:
## Type of issue
<!-- Is this a bug, feature request, question, etc.? Note if this is a documentation issue, please open a ticket here instead: https://github.com/prebid/prebid.github.io -->
Question
## Description
<!-- Describe the issue -->
In the context of the fledgeForGpt module, it's not yet clear how the top-level seller (in this case, GPT) compares contextual bids with those derived from IG signals. In cases of FLEDGE eligibility, adapters can return a tuple consisting of contextual bids and FLEDGE Auction Configs inside the `interpretResponse` function. As described in various issues, we should expect that the top-level runner can choose the winning bid between the 'classic' contextual auction and the FLEDGE one.

Is this assumption correct? If so, how is the comparison performed? Does GPT compare the bid value of the contextual winner with that of the FLEDGE auction? It would be great to have some documentation references, thank you.

## Other information
<!-- References to related issue or PR #s, etc. -->
- https://github.com/prebid/Prebid.js/issues/7634

comment.body: Wrong forum; please ask the gam team

comment.body:
@tpmn-admin we're always looking to improve so I'm interested in more details on what was not working! I posted [here](https://github.com/dgirardi/Prebid.js/commit/30ed60e67f4b6e4c543c498fd7e41327fa5ea706) the changes that I would submit for ortbConverter. Some notes:

 - I was not able to reproduce the video test failure, just following the example seems to work
 - My commit still  has 1 test failure for `✖ should build correct request for banner bid with both w, h`, because ortbConverter sets `format` instead of `w` and `h`. IMO `format` is better because it allows for multiple sizes, but of course it's your choice.
 - GDPR (and USP, GPP, etc) is also handled by ortbConverter, as well as `site`, so I removed those parts. I updated the tests as well since they need to be set up in a slightly different way.
 - Prebid does not expect to find `battr` in either `mediaTypes.video` or `mediaTypes.banner` - it's not in the [list of options for those objects](https://docs.prebid.org/dev-docs/adunit-reference.html#adunitmediatypesbanner). I updated a test case to set it in `params`.

issue.title: TCF2 denied 'fetchBids' for 'bidder.seedtag'
issue.body: ## Type of issue Question/support ## Description We have an issue with our bidder on one publisher where we get this error message `TCF2 denied 'fetchBids' for 'bidder.seedtag'` The problem seams to come from a rule from activity controls, but we are unable to understand the exact issue ## Steps to reproduce Just go on this page https://www.gpfans.com/nl/f1-nieuws/85664/het-tijdschema-voor-de-grand-prix-van-grootbrittannie/?pbjs_debug=true and wait for the error message to appear ## Test page https://www.gpfans.com/nl/f1-nieuws/85664/het-tijdschema-voor-de-grand-prix-van-grootbrittannie/?pbjs_debug=true ### Expected results Seedtag should be recognized as a valid bidder (adapter) and participate in the auction ### Actual results Seedtag bidder rejected from the auction ## Platform details ## Other information
